Definition: a pattern of columns of short parallel lines with all the lines in one column sloping one way and lines in adjacent columns sloping the other way
Example: it is used in weaving, masonry, parquetry, embroidery
Synonyms: herringbone_pattern, design, a, pattern, of, columns, short, parallel, lines, with, all, the, in, one, column, sloping, way, and, adjacent, other, it, is, used, weaving, masonry, parquetry, embroidery
Category: noun.artifact
